definitions.definition: Dominant ; holding sway; having particular power or influence.
of a monarch, ruling in one's own right; often contrasted with consort and dowager
examples: Queen Elizabeth II reigned as queen regnant , unlike her mother Queen Elizabeth The Queen Mother .

main_definition: Reigning , ruling ; currently holding power. [from 15th c.]
secondary_definitions: Dominant ; holding sway; having particular power or influence. [from 17th c.]
( postpositive ) of a monarch, ruling in one's own right; often contrasted with consort and dowager
